 The Glory steals a march in Derby 
 STAR RACER Calcutta: Steal The Glory was first and the rest were nowhere in the 2,000m Calcutta Derby Trial Stakes, the main attraction in Wednesdays eight-event card. The even-money favourite from trainer Daniel Davids yard was ridden to victory by jockey Imran Chisty who also helped the trainer score a treble through Canterbury Rocks and Finesse who claimed their respective events  the 1,400m Smart Ruler Handicap and the Desert Shot Handicap over 1,000 metres..RESULTS				 										1. Prince Blossom Cup 1,400m: (2-1) Aleksei (C.Alford) 1; Rasalas (Chisty) 2. Won by: 1/2; (1-31.216). Tote: Win Rs 24. Fav: Rasalas (1). Winner trained by Bath.				 										2. Great Tribute Handicap 1,200m: (5-3-4-1) Canterbury				 										Rocks (Chisty) 1; Devilish (Islam) 2; Red Sails (Ross) 3; Aptitude (Rajinder) 4. Won by: 1-3/4, 1/2, 6-1/2; (1-20.97). Tote: Win Rs 18; Place: 13, 18; Quinella: 21; Shp: 28; Tanala: 95. Fav: Canterbury Rocks (5). Winner trained by Daniel.				 										3. Smart Ruler Handicap 1,400m: (3-6-4-2) Innovator (Shanker) 1; Razorsharp (Chisty) 2; Le Chaim (Islam) 3; Firing Power (Imran K.) 4. Won by: 3/4, 6, 2; (1-32.45). Tote: Win Rs 100; Place: 39, 22; Quinella: 216; Shp: 41; Tanala: 1,088. Fav: Le Chaim (4). Winner trained by Vijay.				 										4. Elistano Handicap 1,800m: (4-5-2-3) Appetent (Islam) 1; Anniversary Boy (Ross) 2; Flicker (Afzal) 3; Asmodeus (Rajinder) 4. Won by: 1-1/2, 3-1/2, 2-3/4; (2-4.57). Tote: Win Rs 86; Place: 36, 116; Quinella: 573; Shp: 228; Tanala: 5,828. Fav: Dancing Storm (1). Winner trained by Javed.				 										5. Accuser Handicap 1,200m: (2-5-4-6) Allied News (Jugnu) 1; San Juan (Aharwal) 2; Mischevious Notes (Vinay) 3; Desire Lad (Rajinder) 4. Won by: 2, 2-3/4; 1/2; (1-22.67). Tote: Win Rs 62; Place: 21, 37, 18; Quinella: 428; Shp: 104; Tanala: 3,913. Fav: Rapid Return (3). Winner trained by Vijay.				 										6. Calcutta Derby Trial Stakes 2,000m: (5-1-3-6) Steal The Glory 				 										(Chisty) 1; Alterio (C.Alf